div.p:
I hope Dr Hooker will take care of his health in the Orient;



      J. Hooker visited Palestine and Syria during his six weeks of leave in 1860; see J. Hooker to M, 20 October 1860.
 it is not the best place to proceed to in certain seasons for sake of recreation to so labouriously working a savant as your son. However as a medical man he will guard himself I trust [doubly] and will again be able to add to our store of knowledge.
